A vintage-style illustration of a confident peacock with modest, sparse tail feathers strutting proudly past a humble sparrow whose shadow reveals magnificent, elaborate wings spread wide. The scene is set in a misty Japanese zen garden with raked sand patterns and weathered stones. Warm sepia and muted gold tones dominate, with subtle paper texture overlay suggesting aged parchment. The peacock holds its head high with closed eyes while the sparrow quietly observes from a gnarled pine branch. Soft morning light filters through bamboo in the background, creating gentle shadows across the composition.
